    Angular 19 Course by Tech Sharmit
</h1>

Types of Route Guards :-

1.CanActivate 
    Interface : CanActivate   
    Purpose : Controls if a route can be Activated (Enterred) 
    When it runs : Before route navigation
2.CanActivateChild
    Interface : CanActivateChild
    Purpose : Controls if a child route can be Activated
    When it runs : Before navigating to a child route
3.CanDeactivate
    Interface : CanDeactivate<T>
    Purpose : Controls if user can leave (deactivate) a route
    When it runs : Before leaving a route
    
4.CanMatch
    Interface : CanMatch
    Purpose : Controls if a route should even be matched
    When it runs : During route matching
